President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed October 11, 2021, as Columbus Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he acknowledges the contributions of Italian Americans to the country and the painful history of wrongs and atrocities inflicted on Tribal Nations and Indigenous communities by European explorers. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of facing these past episodes honestly and committing to investing in Native communities, upholding Tribal sovereignty, and pursuing a brighter future centered on dignity, respect, justice, and opportunity for all people. President Biden directs that the flag of the United States be displayed on all public buildings on Columbus Day to honor the diverse history of the nation and all those who have contributed to shaping it.